  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The present study will assess whether the size of treatment groups (groups of 10 vs. 30
      participants) affects short- and long-term weight loss. It is hypothesized that participants
      assigned to a small group will exhibit similar short-term and long-term weight losses (i.e.,
      weight loss at months 6 and 12) as compared to those assigned to a large group.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
